cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof search in logics with multiplicative connectives. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses an algebraic method for calculating the distribution of side-formulae in rules, which is relevant to programming language semantics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses search strategies for finding proofs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses methods for solving sets of Boolean constraint equations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses systematic application of the methods to a large family of relevant systems, which is relevant to software engineering.
